# Module Size Splitting

- When a feature folder becomes too large, split by sub-domain before adding more behavior.
- Target structure: `api/`, `components/`, `hooks/`, `lib/`, `types/`, and subfolders by domain (`users/`, `roles/`, `overrides/`, etc.).
- Prefer move-first refactors (no behavior change) before optimization/refinement.

## Split Triggers

- A single feature folder exceeds ~15 files or mixed concerns become hard to scan.
- A single component/hook grows beyond ~250-300 lines and handles multiple flows.
- Frequent merge conflicts happen in the same feature files.

## Required Follow-up

- Add/update index exports after moving files.
- Keep import paths consistent with project aliases.
- Run focused verification for touched areas after each split batch.
